[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     31[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     32[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mA few things worth knowing upfront:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     33[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     34[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mNames are not strings; they are time-varying attributes with effective spans.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Recipe 5.1's matcher compares name strings; recipe 5.7's matcher compares against a name [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173mhistory[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m (current name plus zero or more prior names plus zero or more aliases, each with an effective span). A record arriving with a name dated five years ago compares to whichever name was current for the identity five years ago, not just to the current name. The demo's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mIdentityRecord[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m data structure carries this temporal model.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     35[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDetection comes before resolution.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A flat-name matcher does not need a name-change detector because every name is the value-of-the-day. The temporal model needs an explicit detector because [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173madding a new name to an existing identity[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m is structurally different from [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173ma new record matching an existing identity[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m. The demo separates [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdetect_name_change_candidate[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m from [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mresolve_name_change[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m for this reason.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     36[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDirect and indirect changes route differently.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A direct change is an explicit assertion (the patient said so, the document says so, the payer's update event says so). An indirect change is a high-demographic-match record arriving with a different name from the matched identity. Indirect at high confidence is rare and routes more conservatively than direct at the same confidence band.[K
