[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    2061[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mReal S3 supporting-document and audit-archive buckets.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The supporting-document bucket holds court orders, marriage certificates, divorce decrees, and license scans uploaded by patients (through the patient portal) or staff (at the front desk). SSE-KMS with a customer-managed key, lifecycle-managed retention. The audit-archive bucket is Object Lock in Compliance mode with retention floor at the longer of HIPAA records-retention, state medical-records-retention, identity-document retention, and any research IRB retention. Lifecycle to S3 Glacier Deep Archive after 90 days. Forward audit data events to a dedicated audit AWS account.[K
