[49m[38;5;10m+     1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Expert Review: Recipe 11.1 - FAQ Chatbot
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Reviewed by:** Technical Expert Panel (Security, Architecture, Networking, Voice)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Date:** 2026-05-24
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Recipe file:** `chapter11.01-faq-chatbot.md`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Overall Assessment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is the first recipe in Chapter 11 (Conversational AI / Virtual Assistants) and the chapter's introductory simple-tier recipe. It establishes the chapter's operational discipline (corpus-curation-as-the-project-not-the-LLM, scope-containment-as-make-or-break, layered-scope-defense-in-depth, crisis-detection-as-day-one-floor, persona-as-institutional-not-technical, identity-mostly-absent-for-FAQ-bot, conversation-log-as-PHI-by-association, per-cohort-monitoring-as-launch-gate, hybrid-retrieval-as-default, citation-discipline-as-grounding-honesty-mechanism, refusal-and-handoff-as-feature) and frames the chapter's posture toward chatbots as patient-experience products with engineering as substrate rather than as LLM deployments that happen to interact with patients. The Priya-with-the-parking-question-on-Tuesday-evening vignette earns its position: the dermatology-appointment confirmation email that does not answer the question, the website with eleven PDFs three of which are dated 2019, the chatbot with the button menu that does not contain the parking option, the "Would you like to talk to a representative?" with the "Monday through Friday from 8 AM to 5 PM" follow-up that arrives at 7 PM Tuesday, the closing of the chat window with the "she will figure out the parking situation when she gets there." sets up the institutional-and-economic stakes (patient time, staff time, patient frustration, calls that abandon to the ED because the patient could not figure out a simpler path, the slot-occupied-by-bad-bot opportunity cost) at exactly the right "this is what legacy healthcare chatbots actually produce in production" register.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Technology section is the chapter's introductory pedagogy on the RAG-for-conversational-AI pipeline, and it executes at the right grain for the simple-tier slot. The "Why the Old Healthcare Chatbots Failed" subsection grounds the button-and-decision-tree-product-wearing-a-chat-bubble-UI failure mode in a specific architectural diagnosis (pattern-matching layer mapped utterances to a couple dozen pre-defined intents, fallback to button menu when utterance did not match cleanly, more-content-writers-and-more-branches did not solve the problem, fundamental issue that natural-language questions cannot be enumerated in advance). The "What RAG Looks Like for a Healthcare FAQ Bot" subsection's nine-stage pipeline pedagogy (knowledge-base ingestion, chunking, embedding, indexing, retrieval at query time, generation, citation and grounding, refusal and handoff, logging and audit) is correctly granular for the simple-tier slot. The "What the FAQ Bot Has To Do That a Generic LLM Cannot" subsection's seven-property enumeration (model does not know institution's operational details, model has no real-time updates, model will happily answer clinical questions, model will engage with adversarial prompts, model produces output with compliance implications, model's persona has to be consistent, model has to handle long-tail patient phrasing without doing damage) frames the architectural-grain correctly and is the recipe's clearest articulation of the why-naked-LLM-in-front-of-chat-widget-is-not-an-FAQ-bot primitive. The "Crisis Detection Even For a Simple FAQ Bot" subsection elevates the chapter-pattern crisis-detection-floor primitive from the chapter preface and makes it concrete with the specific keyword-and-phrase-classifier-curated-by-clinical-quality-team-version-controlled-multilingual pattern. The "Scope Containment: The Most Underweighted Discipline" subsection's three-layer defense-in-depth framing (system prompt to LLM, vendor-managed guardrail layer, offline scope-drift review program) is the recipe's strongest single articulation of the layered-scope-discipline primitive. The "Why a Good FAQ Bot Builds the Operational Muscles for Everything Else" subsection's six-discipline enumeration (knowledge-base curation and freshness, prompt engineering and versioning, conversation logging and audit pipeline, scope filtering and refusal patterns, crisis detection and escalation, per-cohort accuracy monitoring) frames the chapter pedagogy correctly and earns its position as the chapter's strongest single FAQ-bot-as-foundational-recipe primitive. The "Where the Field Has Moved" subsection (RAG matured into default architecture, embedding models meaningfully better, hybrid retrieval as default, re-rankers cheap enough to use, guardrails as managed services, multilingual operation more accessible, build-versus-buy economics still favor buy for many institutions) is appropriately forward-looking with appropriate verify-at-build-time hedges and sets up Chapter 11's later recipes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The seven-stage architecture (channel entry, input safety screening, intent and scope classification, retrieval, grounded response generation, output safety screening, audit and log and telemetry) is the right shape. The cross-cutting design points are correctly elevated (knowledge-base content as institutional asset with lifecycle, persona as institutional not technical, identity mostly absent for FAQ bot, conversation log as PHI by association, crisis detection in parallel with intent classification, scope filtering layered, handoff explicit and warm, multilingual as launch consideration, per-cohort monitoring non-negotiable). The Why-These-Services section walks each AWS component back to the conceptual primitive it implements (Bedrock for LLM-and-embeddings, Bedrock Knowledge Bases for managed RAG, Bedrock Guardrails for scope-and-content filtering, optional Lex V2 for richer multi-turn flows, API Gateway and Lambda for chat-channel backend, DynamoDB for conversation state and metadata, S3 for source documents and audit archive, KMS for cryptographic key custody, CloudWatch for operational metrics, CloudTrail for API-level audit, EventBridge for cross-system events, Kinesis Firehose plus Glue plus Athena for analytics, optional Connect for live-agent handoff, Secrets Manager for external integration credentials, WAF in front of chat endpoint).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Honest Take is strong, with eight observations earning the recipe's voice: (1) the technology-is-the-most-ready-and-the-failure-modes-are-the-most-forgiving-and-institutions-most-consistently-underinvest framing as the recipe's central observation; (2) the corpus-as-someone-else's-problem trap (the recipe's strongest single trap, with the corpus-curation-is-the-project-not-the-second-half-of-the-work reframe and the hours-of-operation-scattered-across-three-different-web-pages and the parking-situation-in-the-office-manager's-head and the visit-prep-instructions-five-different-PDFs-three-of-which-contradict-each-other examples); (3) the shipping-with-too-narrow-a-scope trap with the hours-and-locations-only-is-not-worth-deploying observation; (4) the shipping-with-too-broad-a-scope trap with the LLM-components-inherently-disposed-to-attempt-answers-they-should-not framing; (5) the crisis-detection-as-phase-two-feature trap with the "the FAQ bot is a front door; patients in crisis sometimes show up at front doors" observation; (6) the underweighting-the-patient-experience-work-on-the-bot's-persona trap with the patient-experience-team-owns-the-persona framing; (7) the shipping-without-a-plan-for-measuring-quality trap with the containment-rate-is-a-perverse-metric-by-itself observation and the right-metric-mix enumeration; (8) the treating-the-bot-as-a-one-time-build trap with the ongoing-operational-investment framing. The closing sequence ("the thing that surprises engineers coming from generic-chatbot backgrounds is how much of the engineering value is in the unglamorous pieces" / "the thing that surprises healthcare professionals coming from clinical-software backgrounds is how much patient-experience work is in the prompts and the persona" / "the thing about Amazon Bedrock specifically" / "the thing about cost" / "the thing about scope-containment" / "the thing about crisis detection" / "the thing about per-cohort equity monitoring" / "the thing I would do differently the second time: invest more, earlier, in the operational ownership and the governance structures") is the recipe's strongest single closing primitive and frames the FAQ-bot-as-small-project-that-touches-every-part-of-the-institution thesis at exactly the right grain. The closing "the patients who deserve a better front door than the previous generation of chatbots gave them are exactly the patients who will use this one if the institution does the operational work to make it good" line is the recipe's clearest articulation of the patient-dignity-surface primitive in the FAQ-bot context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Variations and Extensions section (multilingual deployment, voice integration drawing from recipe 10.5 patterns, SMS and messenger integration, live-chat queue integration with full handoff, pre-visit reminder integration, provider-directory deep search, persona variants by patient segment, continuous-improvement loop with feedback labeling, FAQ bot as prelude to scheduling and refill bots, embedded in patient portal vs public website, equity-driven content augmentation) is well-scoped and frames each extension at the right grain.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m That said, two correctness-and-compliance gaps at HIGH severity need attention before publication, plus the chapter-pattern set of MEDIUM and LOW items.
