[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The Technology section's "Why the Old Healthcare Chatbots Failed" subsection grounds the button-and-decision-tree-product-wearing-a-chat-bubble-UI failure mode in a specific architectural diagnosis** with the "The fix that did not work was hiring more content writers to expand the decision tree... The fundamental problem was that natural-language questions cannot be enumerated in advance" framing as the recipe's clearest articulation of the why-decision-tree-bots-failed primitive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The "What RAG Looks Like for a Healthcare FAQ Bot" subsection's nine-stage pipeline pedagogy is correct and well-paced.** Each stage is grounded in a specific engineering reality with appropriate verify-at-build-time hedges. The "The retrieval technology is the easy part" framing on knowledge-base ingestion is the recipe's clearest articulation of the corpus-versus-technology-cost-asymmetry primitive.
