[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conversation-log-as-PHI-by-association governance (Security S1) overlaps with the per-cohort monitoring (Architecture A1), the LLM faithfulness check (Security S2), the prompt-injection mitigation (Security S3), and the per-channel authentication (Networking N1).** The Security expert's conversation-log governance framing with the recipe-distinct unauthenticated-public-website-channel and shared-device-and-patient-rights-workflow amplifications is operationally connected to the per-cohort monitoring (the per-cohort metric pipeline operates over de-identified content per the analytics-layer-de-identification discipline; the per-cohort patient-rights workflow ensures that per-cohort metrics do not become a de-anonymization vector), to the LLM faithfulness check (the citation-grounding discipline supports the audit-record-reproducibility per Finding A2; the faithfulness-failure-rate is part of the per-cohort metrics per Finding A1), to the prompt-injection mitigation (the input-screening PHI redaction operates alongside the input-screening prompt-injection detection; the per-language jailbreak-test corpus discipline integrates with the per-language redaction-taxonomy per Finding A3), and to the per-channel authentication (the per-channel session-token discipline is the input-side of the conversation-log governance scaffolding). The five findings reinforce each other; the consolidated fix specifies the conversation-log governance as the architectural primitive with the per-cohort monitoring, the faithfulness check, the prompt-injection mitigation, and the per-channel authentication threading through the same per-channel-and-per-classification mechanism.
