[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring (Architecture A1) overlaps with multi-language deployment (Architecture A3) and accessibility (Architecture A7).** Per-language deployment is an explicit cohort axis; per-language launch-gate per Finding A1 reinforces per-language asset-development per Finding A3. Accessibility cohorts (screen-reader users, keyboard-navigation users, voice-input users via the Variations voice-integration extension) are equity-acute per-cohort populations that benefit from the same launch-gate discipline. The three findings reinforce each other and the consolidated fix specifies per-cohort, per-language, and per-accessibility-affordance as multi-axis cohort dimensions.
