[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **LLM faithfulness check (Security S2) overlaps with prompt-injection mitigation (Security S3) and foundation-model versioning (Architecture A2).** The faithfulness check operates at the output-side; the prompt-injection mitigation operates at the input-side; together they bound the LLM's runtime behavior. The foundation-model and prompt and Guardrails-policy versioning per Finding A2 ensures that a faithfulness regression or a prompt-injection-defense regression is detectable and rollback-able. The three findings reinforce each other.
